# data-editor

## Functionality
An interactive, editable spreadsheet-like data matrix component where users input environmental sample measurements. Supports dynamic columns for multiple samples per parameter, real-time editing, and validation.

## Tasks
- Render editable grid of parameters × sample columns
- Allow adding/removing sample columns dynamically
- Validate numeric input (reject non-numeric values)
- Sync edited values with parent state for compliance assessment
- Display parameter metadata (name, unit, limit, type) as read-only columns

## Purpose
Provides the **primary data entry point** for the entire application. All downstream features (Dashboard, Forecasting, Reporting) depend on the data entered here. A clean, intuitive editing experience is critical for environmental engineers who use this daily.

## General Roadmap
- Currently `components/DataEditor.tsx` (~4.6KB)
- Future: CSV/Excel import directly into the editor
- Future: cell-level validation highlighting (red for out-of-range values)
- Future: bulk paste from clipboard support

## Key Files
- `components/DataEditor.tsx` — DataEditor component
